November 2024 - Back-Channel Logout, Community & Feedback Oppertunities
Happy November, Emil

A huge thank you for subscribing to our Product newsletter in which we share updates around our platform, community activity, upcoming events, and provide some helpful insights on how you can simplify and get the most out of  your identity infrastructure!



Feature highlights
For the month of November, we are excited to share a few new additions to the Zitadel platform, focused on several key features, including: 
Back-Channel Logout

Early November brings Back-Channel Logout into the Zitadel feature lineup! The back-channel logout is a mechanism that resides on the server-side and does not require  the user agent to be involved. The user will be logged out from all clients in the event that the user agent was closed. 
New Translations Added For Upcoming Typescript Login

We are proud to announce we offer translations now for the soon to be released Typescript login for German, Spanish, Italian, and English ! Not seeing the language of your choice? Request or partner with us on enhancing it here [https://github.com/zitadel/typescript/tree/main/apps/login/locales].
Continued Performance Enhancements

It is important that we serve your organization’s needs and by prioritizing performance improvements with our engineering team, we can ensure that Zitadel can continue to bring a best in class experience for you and your customers.



Community & Feedback Oppertunities
